NSS-IIITD Website
temporarily hosted at https://fanciful-mermaid-c9a912.netlify.app/
Description
The NSS-IIITD Website is a platform designed for the National Service Scheme (NSS) chapter at the Indraprastha Institute of Information Technology Delhi (IIITD). 
The website serves as a central hub for information about NSS-IIITD's activities, events, and initiatives. 
It provides a user-friendly interface for both members and visitors to stay updated on the organization's work and participate in various programs.

Table of Contents
* Installation
* Usage
* Features
* Contributing

Installation
To run the NSS-IIITD Website locally, follow these steps:

bash
Copy code
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/nss-iiitd-website.git

# Navigate to the project directory
cd nss-iiitd

#navigate to frontend and backend directories

# Install dependencies in both ns-frontend and nss-backend
npm install

# Create a .env file and add necessary variables

# Start the application
npm start in nss-backend
npm run dev in nss-frontend

Usage
Once the application is running, open your web browser and navigate to http://localhost:5173. Explore the website's features to learn about NSS-IIITD's initiatives, upcoming events, and how to get involved.

Features
Event Calendar: Stay informed about upcoming events organized by NSS-IIITD.
Gallery: View photos and memories from past events.
Join NSS: Learn how to become a member and contribute to social causes.
Contact Us: Reach out to NSS-IIITD for inquiries or collaborations.

Contributing
We welcome contributions from the community to enhance the NSS-IIITD Website. To contribute:

Fork the repository.
Create a new branch: git checkout -b feature/your-feature.
Make your changes and commit them: git commit -m 'Add some feature'.
Push to the branch: git push origin feature/your-feature.
Submit a pull request.
Please follow the code of conduct and contribution guidelines in this repository.
